CHRIS: When l was young

01:01.560 --> 01:04.750
l met this beautiful girl
by a lake.

01:06.460 --> 01:08.360
Ow! Hey! Whoa!

01:08.800 --> 01:10.390
(GIRL LAUGHING)

01:10.460 --> 01:12.800
Scusi! Scusi!

01:15.340 --> 01:18.170
Dov'è la Svizzera?

01:19.040 --> 01:20.370
No capisce.

01:20.440 --> 01:23.810
No capisce?
Où est la Suisse?

01:23.880 --> 01:25.280
Switzerland?

01:25.750 --> 01:27.340
Oh, Suisse. Yeah.

01:27.410 --> 01:30.380
Yeah, Switzerland. Hi.

01:30.450 --> 01:32.210
Oh, you're American?

01:33.050 --> 01:34.950
So are you?
ANNIE: Yeah.

01:37.460 --> 01:41.190
Keep going
till you smell money
or step in chocolate.

01:42.800 --> 01:45.230
Okay. Thank you.

01:50.140 --> 01:52.630
Watch your head.
You okay?

01:52.710 --> 01:53.970
l'm fine.

02:17.860 --> 02:19.390
Can l sit here?

02:22.900 --> 02:24.370
Actually, no.

02:25.040 --> 02:28.410
Two years ago,
l reserved this specific area.

02:29.110 --> 02:30.770
What if l say please?

02:31.610 --> 02:33.600
That's the one exception.

02:49.630 --> 02:50.690
Oh.

02:50.760 --> 02:52.250
Careful there.

03:01.540 --> 03:03.440
You find Switzerland?

03:03.840 --> 03:05.970
Um... l did.

03:07.480 --> 03:09.210
l claimed it for Missouri.

03:09.280 --> 03:13.010
Planted my flag
and sold beads
to the natives.

03:14.920 --> 03:16.950
They had sandwiches there.

03:17.960 --> 03:19.690
l brought you some.

03:26.970 --> 03:28.200
l'm Ann.

03:30.400 --> 03:31.700
Collins.

03:31.770 --> 03:34.000
(lN SWISS ACCENT) The lady
who discovered Switzerland.

03:34.070 --> 03:36.100
Read it all in the papers.

03:36.940 --> 03:38.600
l'm Chris Nielsen.

03:41.410 --> 03:43.710
How did you know
l'd be here?

03:43.950 --> 03:46.150
Um... l didn't.

03:47.190 --> 03:48.550
(CHUCKLING)

04:01.500 --> 04:02.900
(EXCLAIMING)

04:14.110 --> 04:15.840
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

04:18.690 --> 04:20.149
(DOG BARKING)

04:22.960 --> 04:24.860
(lNDISTINCT CHATTERING)

04:40.470 --> 04:42.200
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

04:56.460 --> 04:57.950
Let's make out.

04:58.020 --> 04:59.390
(CHUCKLING)

05:02.600 --> 05:04.120
(ALL LAUGHING)

05:08.840 --> 05:09.960
You've got
to eat something.

05:10.040 --> 05:12.160
No, l don't. l can
get something at school.

05:12.240 --> 05:13.640
l know what!

05:13.910 --> 05:16.100
Well, Mom, l gotta carb up,
l got a game.

05:16.210 --> 05:17.800
And a math test.

05:18.380 --> 05:19.970
Yeah, l'm ready.

05:20.180 --> 05:21.440
l'm cool.

05:23.380 --> 05:25.010
Mom, if you get me,

05:25.090 --> 05:28.450
l won't have
to wait at his
incredibly boring game.

05:28.520 --> 05:30.750
Sorry, Marie,
l have a meeting.

05:31.190 --> 05:33.320
Angie's gonna pick you up

05:33.560 --> 05:35.760
before she gets your brother.

05:36.230 --> 05:38.250
l'll let her take the van.

05:39.700 --> 05:41.760
l'll see your chorus thing
tomorrow.

05:41.840 --> 05:42.890
l thought you couldn't.

05:42.970 --> 05:44.840
l don't wanna miss it.

05:45.340 --> 05:46.860
We're late, guys!

05:46.940 --> 05:48.810
l'll pull out the van.

05:50.910 --> 05:52.970
Hey, ace it, okay?
Yeah.

05:54.780 --> 05:56.040
Love you.

06:02.460 --> 06:03.720
Do you...

06:05.390 --> 06:07.490
Do you want his breakfast?

06:07.560 --> 06:09.050
(HORN HONKING)

06:10.430 --> 06:11.900
(ENGINE STARTING)

06:11.970 --> 06:13.520
You mother puts
healthy stuff in.

06:13.600 --> 06:16.630
Don't trade it...
For chips and cookies.
l know.

06:43.930 --> 06:47.390
CHRIS: lt was the last time
Annie and l saw them alive.

07:03.350 --> 07:06.650
MINISTER:
When death claims
the life of our children

07:08.790 --> 07:12.380
we are left with
too many questions.

07:15.260 --> 07:18.820
How do we make sense
of the feelings
we're left with?

07:21.940 --> 07:24.130
The Gospel according to Luke,

07:24.470 --> 07:25.940
even the First Corinthians,

07:26.010 --> 07:30.570
tell us of
the extraordinary paradise
that awaits us.

07:58.000 --> 07:59.730
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

08:00.710 --> 08:02.940
(WOMAN CHATTERING
ON PA SYSTEM)

08:09.650 --> 08:12.180
Okay. The lucky winner is

08:13.020 --> 08:14.250
Jacobs.

08:14.320 --> 08:15.790
Stacy Jacobs.

08:22.760 --> 08:25.630
Hello, Stacy,
l'm Dr. Nielsen.

08:26.700 --> 08:27.720
Hi.

08:28.470 --> 08:30.030
Ah, too late.

08:31.840 --> 08:33.970
Oh! Nice stream.

08:34.039 --> 08:36.770
He's feeling better.
He waited 10 years.

08:37.480 --> 08:39.570
Stacy Jacobs!

08:41.309 --> 08:43.210
What were you thinking?

08:43.850 --> 08:45.370
lt's all right.

08:45.450 --> 08:47.820
My kid used to say,
"What's the difference?

08:47.890 --> 08:50.080
"You weren't looking anyway."

08:51.120 --> 08:52.750
You like rabbits?

08:53.560 --> 08:55.460
Yes? Then go like this.

08:57.730 --> 08:58.820
Good.

08:59.800 --> 09:00.990
Ready?

09:05.270 --> 09:06.600
(GRUNTING)

09:06.770 --> 09:08.830
We've given her MRls and...
Whoa!

09:08.910 --> 09:10.810
Wild rabbit. Watch out.

09:12.680 --> 09:14.910
And also a CAT scan,
l believe.

09:16.450 --> 09:20.250
Look at that.
Stacy, you have more
pictures than a supermodel.

09:21.120 --> 09:22.610
Do you ever wear glasses?

09:22.690 --> 09:24.890
No, she doesn't need glasses.

09:25.230 --> 09:26.560
Does your head hurt a lot?

09:26.630 --> 09:27.890
All the time.

09:27.960 --> 09:30.020
l want you to
do something for me.

09:30.100 --> 09:33.430
Cup your hand,
cover your nose
and mouth like this.

09:33.500 --> 09:34.590
And just breathe in and out.

09:34.670 --> 09:36.000
WOMAN: (ON lNTERCOM)
Mrs. Nielsen on four.

09:36.070 --> 09:37.590
That's my wife.

09:37.800 --> 09:40.600
lf you can do it longer
than she can talk,

09:41.140 --> 09:42.270
that's an achievement.

09:43.880 --> 09:46.140
Christy,
l've got a meltdown.

09:46.210 --> 09:47.870
Okay, take a breath.

09:47.950 --> 09:50.640
Eight pieces from Germany
never arrived.

09:51.750 --> 09:54.190
l've gotta
choose replacements
the night before the opening,

09:54.250 --> 09:57.620
get them down here
and re-hang them,
re-light them and l...

09:57.690 --> 09:58.710
(SIGHING)

09:58.790 --> 10:00.190
Okay, focus.

10:01.830 --> 10:04.730
lt's our
Double D-anniversary.
l'm ruining it.

10:04.800 --> 10:06.320
Double D, yeah.

10:06.430 --> 10:09.130
l'm sorry, Christy,
l can't leave here.

10:10.100 --> 10:11.430
l'm sorry.

10:15.910 --> 10:19.350
Tell you what,
how about this.

10:20.110 --> 10:22.240
How about the Hudson Rivers?

10:23.680 --> 10:25.240
That gives us three.

10:25.320 --> 10:27.980
And the Hollenbeck,

10:28.690 --> 10:34.180
and the, uh,
Hennik 16, 19 and 23,

10:34.560 --> 10:35.890
and the bridge.

10:35.960 --> 10:37.400
But they're in Fairfield.

10:37.460 --> 10:39.660
l don't have anybody to send.

10:39.970 --> 10:41.200
l'll drop by after work.

10:41.270 --> 10:44.330
l'll get them and take 'em
to the gallery, huh?

10:45.770 --> 10:47.100
You'd do that for me?

10:47.170 --> 10:48.770
Only if you're
incredibly grateful.

10:49.740 --> 10:52.910
Hey, that's a chance
to show yours.

10:53.550 --> 10:55.070
lt's very sexy.

10:59.020 --> 11:00.580
(BOTH BREATHING)

11:01.650 --> 11:03.150
Okay, weirdo.

11:04.290 --> 11:06.780
l'll be home late,
but l'll be home.

11:10.960 --> 11:12.630
l love you, Bella.

11:13.230 --> 11:14.830
l love you, too.

11:16.640 --> 11:17.690
Bye.

11:21.410 --> 11:23.240
Stacy, do you like art?

11:23.310 --> 11:26.210
My wife fixes paintings
and also makes some.

11:26.750 --> 11:31.240
To me, paintings are
the most important interesting
thing in the world

11:31.620 --> 11:33.350
next to your brain.

11:34.020 --> 11:36.110
You feel better, don't you?

11:36.890 --> 11:38.620
(SCOFFS) Migraines.

11:46.400 --> 11:48.600
l said, "l love you, Bella."

11:49.670 --> 11:51.690
l'll always remember that.

11:52.870 --> 11:54.860
At least l got to say it.

11:56.240 --> 11:57.970
(CAR HORNS BLARING)

12:05.550 --> 12:07.210
(TIRES SCREECHING)

12:13.760 --> 12:14.950
(GASPS)

12:28.040 --> 12:29.510
(BABY CRYING)

12:30.240 --> 12:31.230
You all right?

12:31.310 --> 12:32.970
WOMAN: l think so.

12:38.480 --> 12:40.080
(SHUDDERING)
l'm a doctor.

12:40.150 --> 12:41.520
Don't move.

12:41.590 --> 12:43.250
(TIRES SCREECHING)

12:52.170 --> 12:54.460
(MAN CHATTERING
ON POLICE RADIO)

12:58.140 --> 13:00.040
(lNDISTINCT CHATTERING)

13:07.380 --> 13:08.750
MAN: Chris?

13:09.020 --> 13:10.010
CHRIS: Hmm?

13:10.080 --> 13:11.880
Do you know what's happened?

13:12.790 --> 13:14.850
Yeah. l had a bad
piece of fish before bed.

13:14.920 --> 13:16.250
(CHUCKLES)

13:18.490 --> 13:20.150
(MONITORS BEEPING)

13:20.290 --> 13:22.630
Who are you? A doc?

13:23.860 --> 13:25.830
Are you operating on me?

13:27.770 --> 13:29.170
Who are you?

13:30.500 --> 13:32.270
Why can't l see you?

13:33.070 --> 13:34.800
(BEEPING lNCREASES)

13:42.520 --> 13:43.980
(DOG BARKING)

13:45.720 --> 13:48.480
CHRIS: Ginger, you see me?

13:49.120 --> 13:52.110
MAN: (CHUCKLING)
She does. Dogs are different.

13:53.630 --> 13:55.290
Can you see me now?

13:55.360 --> 13:56.420
CHRIS: ls that you, Doc?

13:56.500 --> 13:58.020
Why are you so blurred?

13:58.100 --> 14:00.430
l'll get clearer
when you want me to, Chris.

14:00.500 --> 14:03.090
Confused how you got home
so fast?

14:03.170 --> 14:06.160
Dreams don't deal in time.
Time doesn't count.

14:06.910 --> 14:08.770
(lNDISTINCT MUTTERING)

14:16.580 --> 14:18.310
You've died, Chris.

14:19.390 --> 14:21.180
You have to be a dream, Doc.

14:21.250 --> 14:23.590
Doc, if l were dead,
would l need you to tell me?

14:23.660 --> 14:25.120
l guess you do.

14:25.190 --> 14:26.990
Everyone's different.

14:30.700 --> 14:33.220
l wish
everybody would go home.
l know.

14:33.300 --> 14:35.170
CHRIS: How come
l see everyone?

14:35.230 --> 14:38.030
Everybody but...
l'm the one
you don't want to see.

14:38.100 --> 14:40.100
You don't wanna be dead.

14:41.340 --> 14:43.930
ANNIE: The kids were
so young at that time.

14:44.010 --> 14:46.910
DOC: What you want
to remember is your kids.

14:49.050 --> 14:52.110
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)
When they were still alive.

15:03.860 --> 15:06.800
When she goes to the hospital,
l'm going too.

15:17.240 --> 15:19.300
Marie, Katie's not...

15:21.680 --> 15:24.280
Katie's not going there
to get better.

15:26.320 --> 15:27.480
Sugar?

15:28.690 --> 15:31.780
They're gonna give her a shot,
and it's not gonna hurt,

15:31.860 --> 15:33.090
and she'll fall asleep.

15:33.160 --> 15:35.290
You're going to kill my dog?

15:35.730 --> 15:37.960
l'm going to
help her die, yes.

15:41.330 --> 15:43.960
Honey, she hurts very...

15:47.610 --> 15:48.940
Very badly.

15:49.010 --> 15:51.440
And nothing can help her.
l'm going to stop that,

15:51.510 --> 15:53.240
because l love her.

15:53.380 --> 15:55.250
You're killing my dog.

15:56.880 --> 15:58.370
You get angry.

15:59.320 --> 16:00.910
Death does that.

16:03.460 --> 16:05.320
What'll happen to her?

16:08.030 --> 16:09.120
Um...

16:09.800 --> 16:11.820
She'll go where we all go.

16:13.430 --> 16:15.400
And how can that be bad?

16:20.540 --> 16:22.270
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

16:27.210 --> 16:28.870
IAN: Oh, my leg!

16:32.520 --> 16:34.010
(BOTH SIGHING)

16:35.350 --> 16:37.880
IAN: Thanks for
not listening to Mom.

16:39.590 --> 16:41.560
About what?
l don't know.

16:41.860 --> 16:44.390
Just coming out here.
This whole day.

16:44.460 --> 16:47.330
She didn't want
us doing this, because of

16:47.930 --> 16:49.560
grades and stuff.

16:51.570 --> 16:53.560
Your mother and l talked.

16:56.310 --> 16:58.540
We always
listen to each other.

17:02.050 --> 17:04.450
So, l mean,
what'd you talk about?

17:06.690 --> 17:09.119
About taking you
out of Head-Royce.

17:11.720 --> 17:13.849
The school is wrong for you.

17:17.560 --> 17:19.900
MINISTER:
While this is a time...

17:20.069 --> 17:22.030
CHRIS: Where are we now?

17:23.099 --> 17:26.560
DOC:
Where we all want to stay.
This is your funeral.

17:28.440 --> 17:29.810
(CHUCKLING)

17:30.080 --> 17:32.570
What am l on?
You're real fuzzy.

17:34.180 --> 17:35.980
(MINISTER CHATTERING)

17:40.890 --> 17:43.580
At least you're willing
to see yourself.

17:43.760 --> 17:45.720
You're losing your fear.

17:46.430 --> 17:47.520
Fear?

17:48.160 --> 17:50.150
Thought you disappeared?

17:50.900 --> 17:52.260
You didn't.

17:53.200 --> 17:54.720
You only died.

17:58.000 --> 18:02.440
A woman,
who lost her children
just four years ago.

18:03.640 --> 18:05.980
Every day in
the Lord's Prayer...

18:06.810 --> 18:07.870
Celia.

18:07.950 --> 18:10.420
(CHUCKLING)
Come on. Whoa.

18:11.920 --> 18:13.720
(MINISTER CHATTERING)

18:36.580 --> 18:37.910
(SHUSHING)

19:17.250 --> 19:20.010
This one is a present for me.

19:22.090 --> 19:24.320
lt's our Double D-anniversary.

19:24.720 --> 19:26.690
Kind of our special day.

19:29.030 --> 19:30.960
lt's her version
of our place.

19:31.030 --> 19:32.120
Your place?

19:32.200 --> 19:33.930
Where we first met.

19:35.400 --> 19:38.030
Where we were
going to retire, l guess.

19:39.000 --> 19:40.730
Live out our lives.

19:40.840 --> 19:42.710
Be old farts together.

19:44.610 --> 19:46.010
Right there.

19:46.650 --> 19:48.550
That's our dream house.

19:49.850 --> 19:51.750
That one's me, l guess.

19:53.850 --> 19:55.820
The blurry one is Annie.

19:56.560 --> 19:58.750
Looks a little familiar, Doc.

20:01.090 --> 20:02.420
(LAUGHING)

20:07.300 --> 20:11.240
The funeral is over.
Why is this going on
past the funeral?

20:15.240 --> 20:16.970
ANNIE: Dear Diary,

20:17.140 --> 20:18.800
l'm writing
in your bullshit pages

20:18.880 --> 20:21.400
because my shrink
is crazier than me.

20:22.150 --> 20:24.140
He thinks you're therapy.

20:24.820 --> 20:27.810
He figures,
if two babies can hammer me
into a psycho ward,

20:27.890 --> 20:29.790
what'll l do with this?

20:30.820 --> 20:32.310
He's so stupid.

20:33.490 --> 20:35.860
He thinks he pulled me
through the breakdown

20:35.930 --> 20:37.920
when it was only Christy.

20:38.330 --> 20:40.300
Always. Only Chris.

20:40.830 --> 20:41.990
Jesus.

20:42.500 --> 20:44.800
l was looking through
his postcards.

20:44.870 --> 20:47.000
Paintings were his obsession.

20:47.070 --> 20:50.440
He used art
as another way to love me,
to help me.

20:51.510 --> 20:53.600
To keep us always together.

20:54.280 --> 20:55.750
CHRIS: Annie.

20:58.580 --> 21:00.110
l'm here, babe.

21:01.350 --> 21:02.840
l still exist.

21:05.260 --> 21:07.120
You're thinking of me.

21:07.530 --> 21:09.290
Keep thinking of me.

21:10.660 --> 21:12.290
Come on, with me.

21:13.100 --> 21:15.070
You were always with me.

21:15.170 --> 21:18.870
The people who finished
each other's sentences.
Remember us?

21:21.310 --> 21:24.000
l still exist.

21:26.080 --> 21:27.570
l still exist!

21:31.020 --> 21:32.880
l still exist.

21:35.150 --> 21:36.880
Just write it down.

21:39.430 --> 21:40.920
Write it down.

21:44.930 --> 21:46.520
"This is Chris."

21:47.730 --> 21:49.500
(ANNIE SIGHING)

21:49.770 --> 21:51.960
"This is Chris."

21:59.010 --> 22:00.100
"l

22:02.820 --> 22:04.080
"still

22:08.020 --> 22:09.280
"exist."

22:20.330 --> 22:21.560
Read it.

22:22.470 --> 22:23.700
Read it.

22:54.970 --> 22:56.490
(ANNIE SOBBING)

22:59.340 --> 23:01.670
CHRIS:
Christ, when does it end?

23:02.780 --> 23:04.970
DOC: There's no rules, Chris.

23:05.240 --> 23:07.110
lt ends when you want.

23:07.910 --> 23:09.180
Where were you?

23:09.250 --> 23:10.770
Someplace else.

23:11.620 --> 23:14.520
You think l'm a figment
of your imagination?

23:14.590 --> 23:16.610
lt's real.
She's real.
You're real.

23:16.690 --> 23:17.990
lt's all real.

23:18.060 --> 23:20.390
That's the point
if there is one.

23:21.490 --> 23:24.400
lt's over when you stop
wanting to hurt her.

23:37.140 --> 23:38.770
(ANNIE SNIFFLING)

23:41.450 --> 23:42.680
Forever.

23:54.730 --> 23:56.390
Don't worry, baby.

23:58.460 --> 24:00.490
l'm not leaving you alone.

24:01.070 --> 24:02.300
l'm not going anywhere.

24:02.370 --> 24:03.730
(SCREAMING)

24:07.170 --> 24:08.440
(SOBBING)

24:24.490 --> 24:25.980
Goodbye, babe.

24:30.960 --> 24:32.230
(SIGHING)

24:54.990 --> 24:56.580
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

25:11.300 --> 25:13.070
(lNSECTS CHITTERING)

25:34.560 --> 25:35.930
(CHUCKLING)

25:38.600 --> 25:40.070
(DOG BARKING)

25:53.050 --> 25:54.880
Katie, it's you!

25:56.110 --> 25:57.840
You're young again!

25:58.820 --> 25:59.980
Katie!

26:02.220 --> 26:03.690
Come here, Katie.

26:03.760 --> 26:05.090
(LAUGHING)

26:06.760 --> 26:07.920
Katie.

26:11.400 --> 26:12.860
Come on, hey!

26:12.970 --> 26:14.430
(KATIE BARKING)

26:14.500 --> 26:16.160
Boy, l screwed up.

26:17.170 --> 26:18.830
l'm in dog heaven.

26:28.950 --> 26:32.210
A place where we all go
can't be bad, can it, girl?

27:00.380 --> 27:03.310
Maybe l'm not in your heaven
after all, girl!

27:03.580 --> 27:05.070
Maybe you're in mine!

27:05.150 --> 27:06.620
(KATIE BARKS)

27:12.490 --> 27:14.930
Annie!

27:35.210 --> 27:36.580
(SQUISHING)

27:48.730 --> 27:51.290
DOC: Chris, what the hell
have you done?

27:51.360 --> 27:53.890
That's not how
you use a stethoscope!

27:54.270 --> 27:55.670
Albert Lewis?

27:55.730 --> 28:00.500
Last time you saw me
l was 63, stretched out
on a cardiac ward!

28:00.570 --> 28:01.560
(LAUGHING)

28:01.640 --> 28:03.940
You thought l was old
and decrepit, huh?

28:04.010 --> 28:06.310
Talking about
"Ah, can't go on!"

28:08.080 --> 28:10.710
Who wants to be 63
throughout eternity?

28:11.020 --> 28:12.250
Look at you on the water!

28:12.320 --> 28:14.620
Well, hello! Come on.

28:15.320 --> 28:18.310
Walk along, feel the beat!

28:18.460 --> 28:20.080
Dancing on water!

28:20.390 --> 28:21.920
Smooth as ever!

28:23.600 --> 28:25.220
And that was you,

28:26.300 --> 28:29.360
just now, when l died.

28:30.300 --> 28:33.970
l thought you recognized me,
because you called me "Doc".

28:34.170 --> 28:36.270
Me being your favorite doc.

28:36.610 --> 28:41.600
Could you lend me a hand?
l'm up to my ass
in problems again, Chief.

28:42.550 --> 28:44.680
Oh, Chris.

28:46.890 --> 28:48.220
Come here.

28:49.320 --> 28:51.310
You are still kinda ugly.

28:53.490 --> 28:55.590
You taught me a lot, Chief.

28:55.860 --> 28:57.020
Nice place you got here.

28:57.100 --> 28:59.890
No, no.
Nice place you got here.

29:00.300 --> 29:01.290
Me?

29:01.370 --> 29:03.560
Sure,
you're making all this.

29:04.100 --> 29:08.540
We're insecure at first,
so we need
safety and comfort.

29:08.770 --> 29:10.740
We all paint
our surroundings, Chris.

29:10.810 --> 29:13.940
But you're
the first guy l know
to use real paint!

29:14.010 --> 29:16.610
There's so much here
she didn't paint.

29:18.520 --> 29:20.040
Like that bird.

29:21.390 --> 29:24.690
Annie gave you a start,
like holding onto handrails.

29:24.920 --> 29:26.950
You're creating a world.

29:27.290 --> 29:31.290
From your imagination,
from paintings you love,
anything you want.

29:31.760 --> 29:33.530
Why doesn't it move?

29:33.730 --> 29:35.830
lt will
when you want it to.

29:39.940 --> 29:41.300
(SQUAWKING)

29:42.840 --> 29:45.070
Oh-hoh! You go, boy!

29:45.140 --> 29:46.170
Can l make it dive?

29:46.240 --> 29:47.770
You're the painter now!

29:47.850 --> 29:49.440
lt's your world.

29:49.550 --> 29:51.180
(CHRIS SCREAMING)

29:51.850 --> 29:53.180
(WHOOPING)

29:54.020 --> 29:55.510
Look at it go!

29:56.860 --> 29:58.850
How about turquoise wings?

29:58.920 --> 30:00.260
Turquoise!

30:00.330 --> 30:03.230
And a little mauve,
all right!

30:03.360 --> 30:04.990
(ALBERT WHOOPING)

30:19.810 --> 30:21.440
l didn't do that.

30:21.580 --> 30:22.810
No, l did.

30:22.880 --> 30:25.780
When we're together
it's like dual controls.

30:26.050 --> 30:28.040
Can l make elephants fly?

30:29.250 --> 30:31.350
Didn't Annie paint a house?

30:36.390 --> 30:38.660
Yeah, it's our dream house.

30:41.700 --> 30:43.930
Just a stroll
across the water.

30:45.270 --> 30:47.100
Let's take the shortcut.

30:51.910 --> 30:53.040
Nice shortcut.

30:53.110 --> 30:54.980
lt's easy, look at me!

30:55.210 --> 30:56.270
l'm gonna drown.

30:56.350 --> 30:58.980
ALBERT: You can't.
You're already dead.

30:59.280 --> 31:02.150
Oh. Am l...
Am l really here?

31:03.020 --> 31:05.050
What do you mean by "you"?

31:05.120 --> 31:07.250
Are you your arm
or your leg?

31:07.490 --> 31:09.360
Partly.
Really?

31:09.730 --> 31:11.820
And if you lost your limbs?

31:12.030 --> 31:13.590
l'd still be me.

31:13.670 --> 31:15.290
What is the "me"?

31:15.830 --> 31:17.360
My brain, l suppose.

31:17.440 --> 31:18.700
Your brain?

31:18.770 --> 31:20.800
Your brain is a body part.

31:20.970 --> 31:22.800
Like your fingernail
or your heart.

31:22.870 --> 31:24.900
Why is that the part
that's you?

31:25.880 --> 31:29.310
Because "l" is sort of
a voice in my head.

31:29.380 --> 31:31.650
The part that thinks,
that feels.

31:31.720 --> 31:33.810
That is aware that l exist.

31:39.690 --> 31:43.250
So if you're aware you exist,
then you do.

31:44.330 --> 31:46.530
That's why you're still here.

31:48.930 --> 31:50.460
(KATIE BARKING)

31:50.540 --> 31:51.870
(LAUGHING)

32:00.310 --> 32:03.680
ALBERT: No windows.
What aren't you ready to see,
l wonder?

32:07.950 --> 32:10.750
Drink it.
Think it's coffee
and it will be.

32:11.190 --> 32:12.180
(SIGHING)

32:12.290 --> 32:13.380
Okay.

32:14.190 --> 32:15.590
lt's coffee.

32:17.860 --> 32:19.520
Paint! Acrylic.

32:20.430 --> 32:21.460
(CHUCKLING)

32:21.530 --> 32:23.190
Why is it so hard?

32:23.270 --> 32:24.430
What?

32:24.600 --> 32:26.300
Your brain is meat.

32:26.370 --> 32:28.270
lt rots and disappears.

32:29.010 --> 32:31.700
You thought
that's all there was to you?

32:34.050 --> 32:36.240
Like you're
in your house now.

32:36.720 --> 32:40.240
You're in your house,
it doesn't mean
you are your house.

32:40.320 --> 32:42.810
The house falls down,
you walk away.

32:44.820 --> 32:46.550
But l rebuilt, huh?

32:46.630 --> 32:49.150
You see your body
because you like seeing one.

32:49.230 --> 32:51.660
We're seeing
what we choose to see.

32:53.500 --> 32:55.520
Let me show you something.

33:19.120 --> 33:20.110
Ha!

33:27.900 --> 33:30.430
CHRIS: lt's real.
Where is the paint?

33:30.770 --> 33:34.540
ALBERT:
You don't need it anymore.
This is your world now.

33:37.710 --> 33:39.300
Thought is real.

33:39.680 --> 33:41.670
Physical is the illusion.

33:43.010 --> 33:44.410
lronic, huh?

33:48.390 --> 33:50.290
Where's God in all this?

33:50.360 --> 33:51.850
He's up there.

33:52.590 --> 33:53.680
Somewhere.

33:53.760 --> 33:55.730
Shouting down
that he loves us.

33:55.790 --> 33:57.690
Wondering why
we can't hear him.

33:57.760 --> 33:59.090
You think?

34:01.330 --> 34:02.990
Drink your coffee.

34:05.500 --> 34:06.660
Needs milk.

34:06.740 --> 34:08.540
Don't push your luck.

34:15.449 --> 34:16.940
(BIRDS CAWING)

34:22.420 --> 34:24.820
ANNIE:
What do you think, Christy?

34:27.429 --> 34:28.790
Right here.

34:31.300 --> 34:33.960
Like this? You think?

34:50.750 --> 34:53.270
They say
we live in our minds anyway.

34:55.690 --> 34:59.990
Having you with me,
like this, keeps me happy.

35:03.460 --> 35:05.790
Why do l believe
you can hear me?

35:07.230 --> 35:09.530
Why do l think
you can see this?

35:15.170 --> 35:18.270
CHRIS:
What's that purple tree?
l never saw that.

35:19.710 --> 35:21.270
Let's take a look.

35:21.350 --> 35:23.250
Think you can get there
in eight seconds?

35:23.310 --> 35:26.080
(EXCLAIMING) Eight seconds?
Over there?

35:26.950 --> 35:29.480
Yeah, l just need
a little incentive.

35:42.430 --> 35:43.630
(SIGHS)

35:49.970 --> 35:52.030
Yeah. l can fly.

35:52.610 --> 35:53.700
No!

35:53.780 --> 35:55.340
Can't l do what l want?

35:55.410 --> 35:58.580
l think
you'd be more comfortable
keeping it real.

35:59.550 --> 36:02.750
Think of running fast,
like the Road Runner, okay?

36:08.230 --> 36:09.630
(SNICKERING)

36:09.930 --> 36:11.590
l can handle this.

36:14.670 --> 36:16.260
Adios, muchacho.

36:18.700 --> 36:20.300
Oh, wait! Chris!

36:20.540 --> 36:22.400
Annie!

36:27.110 --> 36:29.600
l bet you're thinking
"Oh, shit!" now!

36:29.680 --> 36:31.050
(SCREAMING)

36:41.090 --> 36:42.460
(SCREAMING)

36:48.570 --> 36:49.800
Yeah!

36:50.000 --> 36:51.230
Go, boy!

36:51.570 --> 36:52.940
(GRUNTING)

36:54.970 --> 36:56.270
(WHOOPING)

36:57.510 --> 36:59.500
Go, Chris, go!

37:13.060 --> 37:14.390
(EXCLAIMS)

37:25.870 --> 37:27.070
Albert!

37:27.770 --> 37:28.970
Albert!

37:37.850 --> 37:39.610
lt's completely new.

37:40.520 --> 37:43.110
The canvas was blank
when l was alive.

37:44.520 --> 37:47.320
How can l see this drawing
after l'm dead?

37:49.530 --> 37:52.220
For an expert
you look pretty surprised.

37:52.660 --> 37:54.630
ALBERT: You two.
A long courtship?

37:54.700 --> 37:55.860
No, actually.

37:55.930 --> 37:57.870
From the first moment,
it was like...

37:57.940 --> 37:59.270
Soul mates.

37:59.670 --> 38:02.110
lt's extremely rare,
but it exists.

38:03.470 --> 38:06.170
Like twin souls.
Tuned in to each other.

38:08.410 --> 38:10.440
Apparently, even in death.

38:12.780 --> 38:15.150
You're reaching each other
through her painting.

38:15.220 --> 38:17.350
lt's nothing l've ever seen.

38:19.920 --> 38:22.260
ANNIE: You can't see it,
can you?

38:25.160 --> 38:26.890
And you never will.

38:35.440 --> 38:36.700
(SIGHING)

38:37.240 --> 38:38.570
(CREAKING)

39:07.840 --> 39:09.330
l love you!

39:47.510 --> 39:49.040
(KATIE BARKING)

39:55.850 --> 39:58.250
CHRIS: Whose footprints
are these?

39:59.390 --> 40:01.620
Don't ask me,
you put 'em here.

40:05.230 --> 40:06.600
(SQUAWKING)

40:14.170 --> 40:15.330
Annie.

40:16.010 --> 40:17.130
Annie!

40:17.210 --> 40:18.970
ALBERT: Chris!
Annie!

40:26.420 --> 40:28.910
Fantasy is not
what you need, Chris.

40:30.220 --> 40:31.850
No, you're right.

40:32.490 --> 40:33.960
l need Annie.

40:36.530 --> 40:37.820
That'll change in time.

40:37.900 --> 40:39.760
Oh, come on, Einstein!

40:40.060 --> 40:42.360
Time's not on my watch
any more!

40:42.430 --> 40:44.420
Time does not exist here!

40:45.070 --> 40:48.840
Wherever it went,
it won't make me
need Annie less.

40:51.480 --> 40:54.040
You'll feel differently,
and so will she.

40:54.110 --> 40:55.170
Man.

40:57.050 --> 40:58.710
You don't know us.

41:00.320 --> 41:01.680
Wish l did.

41:08.960 --> 41:10.120
CHRIS: Marie.

41:11.300 --> 41:12.460
Marie!

41:18.300 --> 41:19.960
Look, it's Tigger!

41:20.400 --> 41:22.130
lt's my daughter's!

41:23.070 --> 41:25.270
Katie tore it up once, and...

41:29.410 --> 41:31.080
She's here, right?

41:32.220 --> 41:33.680
Where is she?

41:36.290 --> 41:39.810
Chris, here is big enough
for all to have
their universe.

41:42.660 --> 41:45.720
That's not why
you haven't seen them yet,
is it?

41:48.000 --> 41:50.130
What does that mean, Buddha?

41:51.340 --> 41:53.630
l wanna see
my children, Albert!

41:56.140 --> 41:58.010
When you do, you will.

42:15.860 --> 42:17.060
Does that hurt?

42:17.130 --> 42:18.360
Mmm-mmm.

42:19.460 --> 42:20.930
That?
Mmm-hmm.

42:21.770 --> 42:23.290
How about that?

42:23.700 --> 42:26.500
l'm gonna keep doing this
till you tickle.

42:30.940 --> 42:33.880
You've got a fever.
lt's going down, though.

42:34.210 --> 42:36.440
Don't you have
to go somewhere?

42:38.720 --> 42:40.340
Wanna play chess?

42:44.020 --> 42:45.680
l could teach you.

42:47.230 --> 42:49.190
Would you teach me that?

43:18.290 --> 43:19.620
Excuse me.

43:22.530 --> 43:24.050
Albert has to work.

43:24.130 --> 43:26.260
He asked me
to meet with you.

43:27.230 --> 43:29.130
Will that be all right?

43:30.270 --> 43:31.500
Leona.

43:31.900 --> 43:33.200
That's a very beautiful name.

43:33.270 --> 43:35.470
He said you've been isolated.

43:36.910 --> 43:39.600
Do you wanna see others?
Perhaps a city?

43:40.310 --> 43:42.910
l would,
but travel makes me nauseous.

43:45.220 --> 43:46.580
(CHUCKLING)

43:49.650 --> 43:51.250
Close your eyes.

43:53.090 --> 43:54.960
l didn't mean forever.

44:06.240 --> 44:07.710
(LEONA LAUGHING)

44:07.770 --> 44:09.430
What do you think?

44:09.970 --> 44:12.070
l'm a little under-dressed.

44:12.340 --> 44:13.830
You look fine.

44:14.110 --> 44:17.550
Till now you've been
painting your world.
This is mine.

44:18.220 --> 44:21.950
ln our city across the river
we have to have
a common vision.

44:23.550 --> 44:25.280
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

44:25.690 --> 44:27.320
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

44:38.040 --> 44:40.130
So, there's work.

44:40.640 --> 44:42.400
Mmm-hmm.
l like that.

44:43.110 --> 44:46.510
Albert, for example,
is sort of a missionary.

44:46.780 --> 44:48.540
He saves lost souls.

44:48.610 --> 44:49.840
Like me.

44:50.380 --> 44:53.580
Hardly. They are the ones
who can't get here.

44:55.350 --> 44:57.120
You mean, from hell?

44:57.190 --> 44:58.450
ln a way.

44:58.590 --> 45:00.560
lt's not what you think.

45:00.660 --> 45:03.130
My work is with animals.

45:03.360 --> 45:04.620
(BARKING)

45:05.700 --> 45:07.600
Katie is an old friend.

45:09.130 --> 45:11.030
ANNIE: Dearest Christy.

45:11.540 --> 45:14.030
l don't know how
this day unraveled on me.

45:14.110 --> 45:16.570
l was so proud of
how l held together through

45:16.640 --> 45:18.540
this endless afternoon.

45:19.540 --> 45:22.070
But, coming home,
l began to lose it.

45:24.320 --> 45:26.410
lf l had walked out that night
for our Double D,

45:26.480 --> 45:29.850
you wouldn't have been
in the tunnel
doing me a favor.

45:30.790 --> 45:33.220
A whole family lost
in car crashes.

45:34.490 --> 45:36.930
Enough to make a person
buy a bike.

45:38.630 --> 45:39.960
(LAUGHTER)

45:41.830 --> 45:43.060
CHRIS: Where are they going?

45:43.130 --> 45:45.860
LEONA: To help others
be reborn on Earth.

45:46.170 --> 45:48.300
Really? Reincarnation?

45:50.510 --> 45:52.140
(PEOPLE SCATTING)

45:56.550 --> 45:58.680
Albert says to cheer you up.

45:59.620 --> 46:02.520
You have difficulty...
Losing my wife, yeah.

46:05.490 --> 46:07.150
And your children?

46:07.930 --> 46:09.690
They died years ago.

46:10.130 --> 46:12.650
That's why l'm worried
about my wife.

46:15.300 --> 46:17.790
They died
in a terrible collision.

46:17.870 --> 46:19.390
The nanny was driving.

46:19.470 --> 46:21.170
lt wasn't her fault.

46:21.240 --> 46:22.730
And your wife?

46:23.740 --> 46:26.180
My daughter
had asked her to drive.

46:26.280 --> 46:28.010
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

46:43.730 --> 46:45.720
lt was a trucker's fault.

46:46.460 --> 46:49.560
But my wife believed
that if she'd been driving,

46:50.170 --> 46:52.760
her protective instincts
would have...

46:55.670 --> 46:57.440
(LAUGHTER CONTINUES)

47:02.310 --> 47:03.640
(SCATTING)

47:05.880 --> 47:07.350
Are you okay?

47:14.430 --> 47:15.950
Come on, Katie!

47:30.240 --> 47:32.470
LEONA:
Where were you just now?

47:33.140 --> 47:35.870
Your mind's been wandering
all afternoon.

47:36.980 --> 47:38.740
Thinking of someone.

47:40.580 --> 47:43.750
Your wife must have
loved her children very much.

47:44.790 --> 47:46.120
Very much.

47:46.820 --> 47:50.120
But you don't have to
break in half
to love somebody.

47:53.430 --> 47:55.630
Tell me a memory of your own.

47:57.540 --> 47:59.500
Say, with your daughter.

48:18.020 --> 48:19.290
CHRIS: Hey.

48:19.360 --> 48:21.450
That's somebody else's art.

48:21.830 --> 48:23.690
What's the difference?

48:24.160 --> 48:26.220
You weren't looking anyway.

48:30.870 --> 48:32.200
Your move.

48:34.410 --> 48:36.700
ls this where
we go when we die?

48:42.580 --> 48:45.310
lt's a dream, baby.
lt's a beautiful one.

48:46.950 --> 48:49.850
But, you know, dreams...
l know, aren't real.

48:50.450 --> 48:51.650
l know.

48:55.490 --> 48:57.650
lt's after midnight.
l haven't won yet.

48:57.730 --> 48:58.850
lt's your first time.

48:58.930 --> 49:01.060
No, l like that
l haven't won yet.

49:01.130 --> 49:03.160
Means you're not cheating.

49:03.800 --> 49:05.960
And when l win,
l really win.

49:07.070 --> 49:08.970
l wanna play till l do.

49:10.040 --> 49:11.440
Unless you wanna stop.

49:11.510 --> 49:13.640
No. Let's play till you win.

49:16.610 --> 49:19.050
CHRIS: She died
three months later.

49:20.020 --> 49:21.880
We played every night.

49:24.620 --> 49:26.610
lt meant the world to me.

49:28.730 --> 49:30.220
She never won.

49:57.890 --> 50:00.880
l didn't look like this
in the body, you know.

50:04.700 --> 50:06.720
We flew to Singapore once.

50:07.030 --> 50:10.870
And my daddy smiled at
the flight attendant who

50:14.410 --> 50:17.500
looked like this
and wore this name tag,
"Leona".

50:17.610 --> 50:19.130
(BOTH LAUGHING)

50:21.110 --> 50:23.310
He said Asian women are so

50:25.280 --> 50:28.550
lovely and graceful

50:30.450 --> 50:31.440
and intelligent.

50:31.520 --> 50:33.620
He didn't mean only.
l know.

50:33.690 --> 50:35.450
lt was something he said.

50:35.530 --> 50:39.590
And l thought,
when l grow up,
l wanna be that.

50:43.200 --> 50:45.030
You still play chess?

50:54.810 --> 50:57.110
l think l waited
for my partner.

51:40.290 --> 51:43.730
ANNIE: l swear that California
is the strangest place.

51:44.660 --> 51:46.030
They push you into it

51:46.100 --> 51:49.190
so you can do it before
your shrink commits you.

51:50.630 --> 51:52.830
Thoughtful legislation there.

51:54.040 --> 51:55.770
Mine is suspicious.

51:56.470 --> 51:58.770
Another week,
he might commit me.

51:58.840 --> 52:00.500
For my own safety.

52:03.710 --> 52:06.310
l had the husband
l was meant to have.

52:06.820 --> 52:08.810
Two spectacular children.

52:09.690 --> 52:13.490
Blessings no one would dare
expect from life.

52:15.390 --> 52:17.490
And the truth is, simply

52:19.700 --> 52:21.220
that it's over.

52:23.070 --> 52:26.130
Just this one loose end
to ravel up.

52:32.140 --> 52:35.700
l didn't get to say goodbye.
You're dead and l blew that.

52:38.850 --> 52:40.940
l don't get to say goodbye.

52:44.050 --> 52:45.950
But l'll tell you what.

52:46.690 --> 52:49.280
Across whatever distance
there is,

52:51.900 --> 52:53.630
l send you my love.

53:08.110 --> 53:09.170
Hey.

53:12.150 --> 53:13.510
Where were you?

53:13.580 --> 53:14.850
Far away.

53:14.920 --> 53:17.250
l got called back.
l was working.

53:19.860 --> 53:22.160
There are no words
to thank you.

53:23.290 --> 53:24.950
For finding Marie.

53:25.060 --> 53:26.290
(SIGHS)

53:28.230 --> 53:30.170
ls she okay?
She's fine.

53:30.630 --> 53:32.400
You'll see her soon.

53:32.670 --> 53:34.400
She sends her love.

53:35.410 --> 53:36.930
Especially now.

53:45.150 --> 53:48.520
We'll gonna go through
something very hard right now.

53:49.190 --> 53:51.420
l'm with you.
You're not alone.

53:54.730 --> 53:56.220
Annie is dead.

54:00.860 --> 54:02.590
She killed herself.

54:07.470 --> 54:10.630
lt's nothing l ever expected.

54:13.680 --> 54:15.910
Like l said,
you don't know us.

54:18.620 --> 54:21.450
ls that
an occupational hazard
of soul mates?

54:21.620 --> 54:23.950
One's not much
without the other?

54:27.360 --> 54:28.880
But she's okay.

54:29.730 --> 54:32.090
Because her pain is over.

54:32.160 --> 54:33.190
You don't understand.

54:33.260 --> 54:35.230
She won't cling like me.

54:35.500 --> 54:37.160
When do l see her?

54:37.300 --> 54:38.460
Never.

54:41.270 --> 54:42.970
You'll never see her.

54:43.040 --> 54:45.940
She's a suicide.
Suicides go somewhere else.

54:46.880 --> 54:48.350
Why are you punishing her?

54:48.410 --> 54:50.740
lt's not punishment.
She's suffered enough.

54:50.810 --> 54:52.780
There are no judges
or crimes.

54:52.850 --> 54:54.010
Everybody's equal.

54:54.080 --> 54:55.980
That's the way things work!

54:56.050 --> 54:58.320
And suicides go to hell?

54:58.590 --> 55:00.720
No goddamn judgment in that!

55:03.630 --> 55:05.220
You wanna fight?

55:06.730 --> 55:09.720
You can hide from it
or understand it.

55:10.670 --> 55:14.330
What you call hell
is for those
who don't know they're dead.

55:14.540 --> 55:18.000
They can't realize
what they've done
or what's happened.

55:19.080 --> 55:21.340
Too self-absorbed in life,
that they...

55:21.410 --> 55:22.710
Self-absorbed?

55:22.780 --> 55:25.410
That doesn't apply to Annie,
all right?

55:26.820 --> 55:28.340
No, it doesn't.

55:28.750 --> 55:30.650
Suicides are different.

55:30.720 --> 55:33.210
They don't go to hell
because they're immoral
or selfish.

55:33.290 --> 55:35.730
They go for
a very different reason.

55:35.790 --> 55:40.030
Each of us has an instinct,
and there's a natural order
to ourjourney.

55:40.160 --> 55:42.130
Annie has violated that.

55:42.700 --> 55:44.360
She won't face it.

55:45.340 --> 55:49.270
She won't realize,
accept what she's done.

55:50.470 --> 55:53.200
She will spend eternity
playing that out.

55:53.340 --> 55:55.110
You still say she's in hell.

55:55.180 --> 55:56.240
Everybody's hell
is different.

55:56.310 --> 55:58.180
lt's not all fire and pain.

55:58.250 --> 56:00.680
Real hell
is your life gone wrong.

56:05.490 --> 56:07.150
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

56:20.440 --> 56:22.100
l'm her soul mate.

56:22.170 --> 56:23.700
l can find her.

56:31.620 --> 56:32.950
You don't understand how...

56:33.020 --> 56:35.920
lt's not
about understanding!

56:36.890 --> 56:39.080
lt's about not giving up.

56:40.720 --> 56:42.850
You said there are no rules.

56:42.930 --> 56:44.360
And the purple tree?

56:44.430 --> 56:46.420
You were
pretty surprised then.

56:46.500 --> 56:49.560
(CHUCKLING)
Hey, if there are no rules,

56:49.770 --> 56:52.570
how can you say
all suicides are the same?

56:52.700 --> 56:54.070
l can't, l can't.

56:54.140 --> 56:57.540
Okay. Or she doesn't know
she's dead?

56:57.610 --> 56:58.700
l can't.
Okay.

56:58.780 --> 57:02.370
No one has ever seen
a suicide brought back!

57:02.450 --> 57:03.910
Stick around, Chief.

57:03.980 --> 57:06.070
You ain't seen nothing yet.

57:12.320 --> 57:14.550
Okay.
You deserve your chance.

57:15.160 --> 57:16.960
We'll find a tracker.

57:24.730 --> 57:26.200
(MAN SINGING)

57:28.710 --> 57:30.640
(lNDISTINCT CHATTERING)

57:42.790 --> 57:44.280
(MAN SHOUTING)

58:18.320 --> 58:19.880
(WOMEN SINGING)

58:24.630 --> 58:26.530
(lNDISTINCT CHATTERING)

58:38.180 --> 58:39.570
ALBERT: Hey!

58:46.720 --> 58:49.050
This the guy
who doesn't give up?

58:50.390 --> 58:53.790
Anyone tell you
too much persistence
can get stupid?

58:54.190 --> 58:55.560
Constantly.

58:55.890 --> 58:57.330
l hear the same thing.

58:57.390 --> 58:59.520
l also hear l read too slow.

59:00.130 --> 59:01.930
l don't need glasses.

59:02.530 --> 59:05.160
Eyes being a figment
of my imagination.

59:06.900 --> 59:09.370
You'll hear a lot
of smart stuff here.

59:09.440 --> 59:11.030
lt's usually right.

59:11.110 --> 59:12.370
Don't let it screw you up.

59:12.440 --> 59:13.670
l won't.

59:14.840 --> 59:17.040
Your wife love you as strong?

59:25.620 --> 59:27.150
We'll find her.

59:27.990 --> 59:29.790
But when you find her,

59:30.560 --> 59:33.050
nothing will make her
recognize you.

59:34.000 --> 59:36.230
Nothing will break her denial.

59:37.400 --> 59:39.530
lt's stronger than her love.

59:39.900 --> 59:42.200
ln fact,
reinforced by her love.

59:43.870 --> 59:46.500
You can say everything
you long to say.

59:47.440 --> 59:49.110
lncluding goodbye.

59:49.610 --> 59:51.910
Even if she
can't understand it.

59:53.680 --> 59:57.050
You'll have the satisfaction
that you didn't give up.

59:59.490 --> 01:00:01.360
That has to be enough.

01:00:01.890 --> 01:00:04.420
Get me there.
l decide what's enough.

01:00:06.830 --> 01:00:08.460
When do we leave?

01:00:10.370 --> 01:00:11.960
Close your eyes.

01:00:23.780 --> 01:00:25.750
CHRIS: Albert's a sweet kid.

