01:03:40.780 --> 01:03:42.870
Don't you think
l can make it?

01:03:42.950 --> 01:03:44.970
lf l really dig in...

01:03:45.080 --> 01:03:47.310
You have to show me more!

01:03:47.380 --> 01:03:50.050
Come on!
You're blowing it, lan!

01:03:50.350 --> 01:03:51.750
l'm not you!

01:04:18.750 --> 01:04:20.050
(MOANING)

01:04:59.590 --> 01:05:00.950
Shipwrecks.

01:05:01.960 --> 01:05:03.220
What is this place?

01:05:03.290 --> 01:05:05.090
The gateway to hell.

01:05:09.600 --> 01:05:12.430
How are we doing?
Picking up any signals?

01:05:13.100 --> 01:05:15.540
Actually, not a ripple.

01:05:16.370 --> 01:05:19.370
That's because
l was thinking
of somebody else.

01:05:27.150 --> 01:05:31.780
lt's a slap in the face
when you see
kids taking a test

01:05:31.850 --> 01:05:34.120
and they're just
breezing through it.

01:05:34.190 --> 01:05:36.590
And for you
it just kinda goes.

01:05:37.660 --> 01:05:39.190
Every day l see

01:05:40.260 --> 01:05:43.460
how l'm not as good as you
and everyone else.

01:05:45.370 --> 01:05:47.670
But that doesn't mean
l give up.

01:05:53.240 --> 01:05:54.640
ALBERT: Hey.

01:06:02.750 --> 01:06:04.080
(CLANGING)

01:06:08.460 --> 01:06:10.120
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

01:06:35.390 --> 01:06:36.850
(MEN GRUNTING)

01:06:36.920 --> 01:06:39.150
ALBERT:
Cerberus, the guardian.

01:06:54.700 --> 01:06:56.300
How do you feel?

01:06:58.880 --> 01:07:01.070
More than l want you
in or out of some school,

01:07:01.140 --> 01:07:04.670
l want to know how you feel
when you go to bed at night.

01:07:07.080 --> 01:07:08.480
Real scared.

01:07:10.820 --> 01:07:12.790
l know l believe in you.

01:07:15.220 --> 01:07:17.720
lf l was going through
fucking hell,

01:07:18.030 --> 01:07:21.460
l'd only want one person
in the goddamn world with me.

01:07:33.110 --> 01:07:34.630
(CHOIR SINGING)

01:07:41.020 --> 01:07:42.490
There's a man

01:07:44.150 --> 01:07:46.020
lan never got to know.

01:07:48.990 --> 01:07:50.320
The man

01:07:51.060 --> 01:07:53.030
he was growing up to be.

01:07:57.370 --> 01:08:00.270
He's a good-looking,
clear-eyed young fella,

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:02.270
about 25.

01:08:05.540 --> 01:08:07.030
l can see him.

01:08:10.650 --> 01:08:13.480
He's the type of guy
men want to be around.

01:08:14.550 --> 01:08:16.990
Because he has integrity,
you know?

01:08:19.060 --> 01:08:20.680
He has character.

01:08:21.660 --> 01:08:23.420
You can't fake that.

01:08:26.930 --> 01:08:29.830
And he's a guy
women want to be around, too.

01:08:33.640 --> 01:08:36.040
Because there's
tenderness in him.

01:08:37.170 --> 01:08:38.370
Respect.

01:08:39.640 --> 01:08:40.970
Loyalty.

01:08:41.540 --> 01:08:42.880
Courage.

01:08:45.779 --> 01:08:47.810
And women respond to that.

01:08:50.950 --> 01:08:53.149
Makes him a terrific husband.

01:08:55.290 --> 01:08:57.160
l see him as a father.

01:08:59.229 --> 01:09:01.460
That's where he really shines.

01:09:06.040 --> 01:09:09.490
See, when he looks
in his kid's eyes,

01:09:12.380 --> 01:09:15.370
and the kid knows
that his dad
really sees him,

01:09:16.550 --> 01:09:18.210
he sees who he is.

01:09:19.979 --> 01:09:24.149
Then that child knows
that he is an amazing person.

01:09:26.790 --> 01:09:28.380
He's quite a guy

01:09:29.490 --> 01:09:31.620
that l'll never get to meet.

01:09:34.930 --> 01:09:36.399
l wish l had.

01:09:41.170 --> 01:09:42.600
Let's do it.

01:09:46.080 --> 01:09:48.700
ALBERT: Come on,
she could be in there!

01:09:49.580 --> 01:09:51.050
(MEN GRUNTING)

01:09:58.090 --> 01:09:59.610
(MEN SCREAMING)

01:10:05.560 --> 01:10:06.960
No!

01:10:08.160 --> 01:10:09.720
No!

01:10:10.470 --> 01:10:12.730
Don't! Don't!

01:10:13.500 --> 01:10:14.990
Don't do this!

01:10:15.240 --> 01:10:17.540
Your mother's
not in there, lan!

01:10:24.710 --> 01:10:26.940
Your mom is not in there, son.

01:10:33.960 --> 01:10:35.220
(SOBBING)

01:10:43.200 --> 01:10:46.360
