01:18:24.330 --> 01:18:25.990
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

01:18:29.160 --> 01:18:30.690
(ALL SCREAMING)

01:18:36.970 --> 01:18:38.240
(GASPING)

01:18:58.460 --> 01:18:59.860
Angel Falls.

01:19:01.660 --> 01:19:03.000
(WHISTLES)

01:19:03.770 --> 01:19:05.960
lt's a little expensive,
yeah.

01:19:06.740 --> 01:19:08.860
But it's our first Double D.

01:19:09.040 --> 01:19:11.130
Shouldn't it be incredible?

01:19:14.210 --> 01:19:16.540
l've never seen
anything like it.

01:19:16.880 --> 01:19:18.400
That's my role.

01:19:19.650 --> 01:19:21.950
To bring adventure
to your life.

01:19:26.560 --> 01:19:28.350
You taught me

01:19:29.390 --> 01:19:33.060
the one thing, the only thing
l should always remember.

01:19:35.000 --> 01:19:36.260
Which is?

01:19:38.970 --> 01:19:40.230
l forgot.

01:19:46.740 --> 01:19:48.870
Oh yeah, oh yeah, oh yeah...

01:19:50.450 --> 01:19:52.310
lt was, never give up.

01:19:55.550 --> 01:19:57.040
Never give up.

01:20:01.290 --> 01:20:02.450
Never.

01:20:05.660 --> 01:20:06.890
(GASPING)

01:20:10.870 --> 01:20:12.630
TRACKER: She's here.

01:20:15.040 --> 01:20:16.530
You found her.

01:20:17.040 --> 01:20:19.060
(CHRIS PANTING)
lmpressive.

01:20:19.480 --> 01:20:22.210
That jolt of fear for her.
lt connected.

01:20:22.910 --> 01:20:25.240
CHRIS: My God,
is that our house?

01:20:29.150 --> 01:20:30.480
(CRACKING)

01:20:31.520 --> 01:20:32.920
(EXCLAIMING)

01:20:46.870 --> 01:20:48.230
lt's like our home.

01:20:48.300 --> 01:20:50.330
TRACKER: Don't think that.

01:20:50.670 --> 01:20:52.300
lt's an illusion.

01:20:52.710 --> 01:20:55.140
The whole place.
Her illusion.

01:20:56.250 --> 01:20:58.370
Suicides can get tortured,

01:20:58.450 --> 01:21:00.710
committed to
punishing themselves.

01:21:00.780 --> 01:21:02.750
Don't push her that way.

01:21:02.850 --> 01:21:04.620
You want to see her.

01:21:05.150 --> 01:21:07.350
Tell her
what's in your heart.

01:21:07.620 --> 01:21:09.020
And then go.

01:21:09.490 --> 01:21:10.580
No pressure.

01:21:10.660 --> 01:21:12.290
Wait! Wait! Wait.

01:21:13.030 --> 01:21:14.890
l knew you'd find her.

01:21:15.000 --> 01:21:17.430
You're a competitor
with a big ego.

01:21:17.830 --> 01:21:20.530
How do you know
the first thing about me?

01:21:20.900 --> 01:21:22.800
You called your son Albert.

01:21:22.870 --> 01:21:24.270
Who is that?

01:21:24.910 --> 01:21:27.100
First doctor
l interned under.

01:21:29.310 --> 01:21:31.300
He was like a father to me.

01:21:31.380 --> 01:21:33.970
His words were gold.
A brilliant mind.

01:21:34.680 --> 01:21:37.880
What did he practice
before turning to pediatrics?

01:21:40.920 --> 01:21:43.020
Child psychia...
Psychiatry.

01:21:45.330 --> 01:21:48.230
And he was always
a slow reader.

01:21:50.470 --> 01:21:53.630
But these used to be rimless.

01:21:55.400 --> 01:21:57.070
And the rest of me

01:21:58.340 --> 01:21:59.970
used to be black.

01:22:11.420 --> 01:22:14.980
You know why we chose
to look different?
Me, the children?

01:22:15.990 --> 01:22:18.260
Package doesn't count?
One's as good as...

01:22:18.330 --> 01:22:20.960
No. The old roles
of authority.

01:22:21.030 --> 01:22:23.460
Who's the teacher,
who's the father

01:22:23.530 --> 01:22:26.900
gets in the way
of who we really are,
to each other.

01:22:28.400 --> 01:22:29.460
(SIGHING)

01:22:29.540 --> 01:22:33.000
l've waited for years
for a chance
to watch out for you.

01:22:34.280 --> 01:22:36.610
And l'm watching out
for you now.

01:22:37.010 --> 01:22:40.410
But this isn't like
the rest of hell.

01:22:40.480 --> 01:22:44.540
You've got no defense
against Annie.

01:22:45.050 --> 01:22:49.050
lf losing yourself
or being swallowed
by hell itself

01:22:49.120 --> 01:22:53.580
could save her,
l'd be there
cheering you on.

01:22:55.600 --> 01:22:58.000
You've got
your children back now.

01:22:58.700 --> 01:23:00.190
They need you.

01:23:01.340 --> 01:23:04.640
Three minutes. Any more,
you could lose your mind.

01:23:06.040 --> 01:23:08.100
CHRIS:
How can you lose your mind?

01:23:08.180 --> 01:23:10.870
TRACKER: Once her reality
becomes yours,

01:23:11.380 --> 01:23:13.470
there's really no way back.

01:23:30.400 --> 01:23:32.370
ALBERT: Think about Mom.

01:23:34.070 --> 01:23:36.470
What you said
to bring her back.

01:23:49.520 --> 01:23:50.640
Hello?

01:23:50.720 --> 01:23:51.810
(ECHOING)

01:23:51.890 --> 01:23:53.550
Your door is open.

01:24:03.500 --> 01:24:05.020
(WOOD CREAKING)

01:24:24.820 --> 01:24:26.010
(GASPS)

01:24:26.790 --> 01:24:30.220
Sorry.
l didn't mean to scare you.

01:24:33.360 --> 01:24:35.350
(STUTTERING) Who are you?

01:24:36.470 --> 01:24:38.190
l'm your neighbor.

01:24:38.970 --> 01:24:41.800
l bought the Gormans' place
two months ago.

01:24:42.140 --> 01:24:43.730
l just moved in.

01:24:44.640 --> 01:24:47.130
l never heard
they sold their place.

01:24:48.880 --> 01:24:51.040
You're Annie Nielsen, right?

01:24:52.550 --> 01:24:54.740
They told me a lot about you.

01:24:55.250 --> 01:24:57.280
Like what?
What did they say?

01:24:57.350 --> 01:24:59.790
That you're
a very talented artist,

01:25:00.220 --> 01:25:02.590
and work for a museum,
right?

01:25:03.560 --> 01:25:05.290
And you're a widow.

01:25:06.060 --> 01:25:08.550
Mrs. Gorman
admires your roses

01:25:10.200 --> 01:25:11.530
very much.

01:25:13.440 --> 01:25:15.300
They were so handsome.

01:25:17.510 --> 01:25:20.940
But now
there's no water pressure
in the neighborhood.

01:25:22.110 --> 01:25:25.640
There's no electricity
and no gas.

01:25:28.380 --> 01:25:30.880
There are other things
missing, too.

01:25:30.950 --> 01:25:33.890
Like clean clothes
and books l want to read.

01:25:33.960 --> 01:25:35.320
And, um,

01:25:35.920 --> 01:25:40.490
some of
my favorite paintings
l have to work on.

01:25:40.830 --> 01:25:42.160
(RUMBLING)

01:25:43.500 --> 01:25:44.860
(SCREAMING)

01:25:46.640 --> 01:25:48.190
What is it?

01:25:48.300 --> 01:25:50.470
They're everywhere now!

01:25:52.340 --> 01:25:53.600
l got it!

01:25:57.210 --> 01:25:58.540
lt's gone.

01:26:05.390 --> 01:26:06.720
Thank you.

01:26:09.060 --> 01:26:10.490
You're welcome.

01:26:10.560 --> 01:26:12.990
You say your paintings
are missing.

01:26:13.460 --> 01:26:16.730
Some of my most
precious panels.

01:26:16.800 --> 01:26:18.770
The ones that remind me.

01:26:27.780 --> 01:26:30.470
Remind me of my husband
and my children.

01:26:31.350 --> 01:26:33.510
That's why l never leave.

01:26:35.280 --> 01:26:37.310
Because they might return?

01:26:40.060 --> 01:26:42.550
l hope that's true
with all my heart.

01:26:42.620 --> 01:26:44.350
lt's not, you know.

01:26:45.730 --> 01:26:48.420
When you're dead,
you disappear.

01:26:52.300 --> 01:26:56.030
My wife committed suicide
after our children died.

01:26:56.910 --> 01:26:58.240
After l...

01:27:00.010 --> 01:27:02.200
She was the loveliest person.

01:27:03.850 --> 01:27:05.940
Don't you think that's sad?

01:27:06.450 --> 01:27:07.880
Don't you have to leave?

01:27:07.950 --> 01:27:09.880
No. But if
you want me to go...

01:27:09.950 --> 01:27:11.480
l do.
All right.

01:27:13.720 --> 01:27:17.280
The last day l saw my wife
it was our anniversary.

01:27:17.360 --> 01:27:18.760
Aren't you leaving?

01:27:18.830 --> 01:27:19.850
ln a minute.

01:27:19.930 --> 01:27:23.390
l was sticking around
in case there was
another problem.

01:27:23.530 --> 01:27:25.830
lt wasn't
a wedding anniversary.

01:27:26.100 --> 01:27:28.630
lt was a very
special kind of day

01:27:31.970 --> 01:27:33.940
no one else knows about.

01:27:44.290 --> 01:27:45.810
(ANNIE HUMMING)

01:27:49.820 --> 01:27:51.690
l need to talk to you.

01:27:52.990 --> 01:27:55.190
And you don't
have to respond.

01:28:02.340 --> 01:28:04.310
This is a one-way ticket

01:28:05.240 --> 01:28:06.430
for me.

01:28:08.640 --> 01:28:11.440
My hanging around here
is not helping you.

01:28:11.710 --> 01:28:13.480
And it's killing me.

01:28:14.220 --> 01:28:16.980
Today is kind of a D-Day.

01:28:18.620 --> 01:28:21.060
"D" for decision, l guess.

01:28:24.860 --> 01:28:26.350
About divorce.

01:28:28.530 --> 01:28:30.760
That'd be two D's,
wouldn't it?

01:28:36.540 --> 01:28:38.200
l stand corrected.

01:28:44.250 --> 01:28:47.810
Look what happens
when you don't say anything
for a month.

01:28:50.420 --> 01:28:51.890
Cindy called.

01:28:52.390 --> 01:28:55.020
She said
everything is waiting for you.

01:28:56.620 --> 01:29:00.650
The artists and curators
will see you
when you're better.

01:29:03.260 --> 01:29:04.760
And l told her

01:29:05.570 --> 01:29:08.900
it was the museum
and one of those meetings

01:29:10.940 --> 01:29:13.430
that kept you
from driving that day.

01:29:16.480 --> 01:29:19.680
And if you went back,
it'd mean you weren't sorry,

01:29:20.280 --> 01:29:24.150
you weren't wrong
and you'd be
betraying your children.

01:29:25.620 --> 01:29:29.220
She called you crazy,
and l called her
a soulless bitch!

01:29:29.290 --> 01:29:30.720
And l hung up!

01:29:30.790 --> 01:29:32.780
That didn't go very well!

01:29:38.170 --> 01:29:40.500
What's true in our minds
is true.

01:29:41.870 --> 01:29:44.310
Whether some people
know it or not.

01:29:46.210 --> 01:29:49.270
That's when l realized
l'm part of the problem.

01:29:50.750 --> 01:29:52.740
Not because l remind you.

01:29:54.750 --> 01:29:57.080
But, because
l couldn't join you.

01:29:58.590 --> 01:30:00.350
So l left you alone.

01:30:08.430 --> 01:30:10.190
Don't give up, okay?

01:30:22.810 --> 01:30:23.900
Okay.

01:30:25.450 --> 01:30:26.540
Okay.

01:30:28.320 --> 01:30:29.650
lt's okay.

01:30:47.600 --> 01:30:49.040
ANNIE: So you reconciled?

01:30:52.610 --> 01:30:54.410
That's very romantic.

01:30:56.950 --> 01:30:58.940
She still killed herself.

01:31:00.580 --> 01:31:01.980
ln the end,
she gave up.

01:31:02.150 --> 01:31:03.450
There's nothing
wrong with it.

01:31:03.520 --> 01:31:04.780
Her husband thought so.

01:31:04.850 --> 01:31:06.450
He was a coward!

01:31:07.290 --> 01:31:09.480
Being strong,
not giving up,

01:31:10.360 --> 01:31:12.450
that was his place to hide.

01:31:13.560 --> 01:31:15.860
He pushed away
the pain so hard,

01:31:16.130 --> 01:31:19.690
he disconnected himself
from the person
he loved the most.

01:31:23.100 --> 01:31:25.510
Sometimes,
when you win, you lose.

01:31:34.180 --> 01:31:35.910
When he saw
his children again...

01:31:36.220 --> 01:31:38.620
l thought
your children were dead.

01:31:40.760 --> 01:31:42.350
You can see the dead.

01:31:42.490 --> 01:31:44.980
ln your dreams.
lf you want to.

01:31:49.330 --> 01:31:51.090
l wanna see Christy.

01:31:53.430 --> 01:31:54.960
l can show you.

01:31:55.040 --> 01:31:56.530
lt's not hard.

01:31:57.210 --> 01:31:58.540
All you have to do...

01:31:58.610 --> 01:32:00.340
it's like painting a picture.

01:32:00.410 --> 01:32:02.070
We do it together.

01:32:03.280 --> 01:32:05.080
Just close your eyes.

01:32:06.680 --> 01:32:08.670
Please don't be afraid.

01:32:12.390 --> 01:32:14.690
Remember where
you were married?

01:32:21.730 --> 01:32:22.960
Christy!

01:32:23.730 --> 01:32:25.060
Christy...

01:32:27.140 --> 01:32:30.130
Who else would you
be marrying in your dreams?

01:32:32.510 --> 01:32:34.170
l missed you so.

01:32:37.010 --> 01:32:38.240
Annie...

01:32:39.350 --> 01:32:40.820
This is real.

01:32:44.290 --> 01:32:46.150
The man in the garden.

01:32:50.360 --> 01:32:51.760
lt's me.

01:32:55.300 --> 01:32:56.420
No!

01:32:56.700 --> 01:32:57.860
No!

01:33:00.000 --> 01:33:01.940
Whoever you are,

01:33:02.000 --> 01:33:04.730
did you think
you could take him from me?

01:33:19.690 --> 01:33:21.280
l'm sorry, babe.

01:33:22.090 --> 01:33:23.720
There's some things
l have to say.

01:33:24.430 --> 01:33:26.220
l've only got
a few moments left.

01:33:29.930 --> 01:33:33.270
l'm sorry for all the things
l'll never give you.

01:33:34.040 --> 01:33:37.560
l'll never buy you another
meatball sub
with extra sauce.

01:33:38.370 --> 01:33:40.270
That was a big one.

01:33:42.110 --> 01:33:44.140
l'll never make you smile.

01:33:46.980 --> 01:33:49.470
l just wanted us
to be old together.

01:33:50.590 --> 01:33:54.490
Two old farts laughing
at each other
as our bodies fell apart.

01:33:55.560 --> 01:33:57.320
Together at the end.

01:33:57.490 --> 01:33:59.690
By that lake
in your painting.

01:34:00.730 --> 01:34:02.720
That was our heaven, see?

01:34:04.300 --> 01:34:06.530
There's lots of things
to miss.

01:34:08.140 --> 01:34:10.330
Books, naps,

01:34:11.440 --> 01:34:15.100
kisses...and fights.

01:34:16.010 --> 01:34:18.310
Oh, God,
we had some great ones!

01:34:19.550 --> 01:34:21.350
Thank you for those.

01:34:23.690 --> 01:34:25.880
Thank you for every kindness.

01:34:28.290 --> 01:34:30.380
Thank you for our children.

01:34:31.160 --> 01:34:33.360
For the first time l saw them.

01:34:35.130 --> 01:34:38.690
Thank you for being someone
l was always proud
to be with.

01:34:41.840 --> 01:34:43.330
For your guts,

01:34:44.010 --> 01:34:45.730
for your sweetness.

01:34:46.710 --> 01:34:50.040
For how you always looked,
for how l always wanted
to touch you.

01:34:53.010 --> 01:34:54.880
God, you were my life.

01:34:57.920 --> 01:35:00.620
l apologize for every time
l failed you.

01:35:02.190 --> 01:35:03.950
Especially this one.

01:35:27.180 --> 01:35:29.380
Didn't you think
l'd make it?

01:35:29.880 --> 01:35:31.550
You were in there a while.

01:35:31.890 --> 01:35:34.150
Took me a while to realize
you were right.

01:35:35.060 --> 01:35:37.460
Nothing you can do
could help her.

01:35:38.360 --> 01:35:40.230
This trip was for you.

01:35:43.560 --> 01:35:44.590
Did you come close...

01:35:44.670 --> 01:35:46.220
To losing it?

01:35:46.670 --> 01:35:47.930
Oh, yeah.

01:35:48.970 --> 01:35:51.100
Pushed it right to the edge.

01:35:52.770 --> 01:35:54.800
That's why
l had to come out now.

01:35:54.980 --> 01:35:56.710
l'm giving up.

01:36:00.080 --> 01:36:01.950
Not the way you think.

01:36:06.520 --> 01:36:07.920
Go home, Al.

01:36:09.490 --> 01:36:12.080
Will you tell my children
l love them?

01:36:13.860 --> 01:36:16.090
And l won't
leave their mother.

01:36:21.000 --> 01:36:22.200
Thanks.

01:36:29.710 --> 01:36:31.470
Where are we headed?

01:36:33.250 --> 01:36:35.440
ln one minute
l won't know you

01:36:35.750 --> 01:36:37.980
any better
than you'll know me.

01:36:40.050 --> 01:36:41.920
But we'll be together.

01:36:43.190 --> 01:36:44.780
Where we belong.

01:36:46.890 --> 01:36:48.490
Good people go to hell

01:36:48.560 --> 01:36:51.160
because they can't
forgive themselves.

01:36:52.000 --> 01:36:53.520
l know l can't.

01:36:54.670 --> 01:36:56.540
But l can forgive you.

01:36:57.810 --> 01:36:59.770
For killing my children?

01:37:01.440 --> 01:37:03.240
And my sweet husband?

01:37:04.810 --> 01:37:05.870
No.

01:37:07.010 --> 01:37:10.380
For being so wonderful,
a guy would choose hell
over heaven,

01:37:10.490 --> 01:37:12.450
just to hang around you.

01:37:18.490 --> 01:37:20.590
Not because l remind you,

01:37:21.700 --> 01:37:23.990
but because
l couldn't join you.

01:37:25.300 --> 01:37:27.200
Sorry l left you alone.

01:37:30.000 --> 01:37:31.770
Don't give up, okay?

01:37:52.130 --> 01:37:53.360
Christy?

01:37:59.370 --> 01:38:00.630
Christy.

01:38:05.010 --> 01:38:07.130
What happened to this place?

01:38:10.780 --> 01:38:12.110
lt's cold.

01:38:12.910 --> 01:38:14.250
(CREAKING)

01:38:16.480 --> 01:38:17.820
(CRACKING)

01:38:25.590 --> 01:38:26.820
Christy?

01:38:27.730 --> 01:38:30.430
God, no! No, no, no, no!

01:38:30.500 --> 01:38:33.260
Don't give up!
Don't give up! Christy!

01:38:33.330 --> 01:38:36.330
Don't give up!
Don't, don't give up!

01:38:36.640 --> 01:38:37.870
Christy!

01:38:41.910 --> 01:38:44.310
(FADING)
Christy, don't give up...

01:39:06.330 --> 01:39:07.560
Christy.

01:39:16.880 --> 01:39:18.470
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

01:39:44.240 --> 01:39:45.300
Hey!

01:39:48.440 --> 01:39:49.840
Remember me?

01:40:00.820 --> 01:40:02.790
Sometimes, when you lose

01:40:04.030 --> 01:40:05.250
you win.

01:41:00.450 --> 01:41:02.210
How did we get here?

01:41:06.220 --> 01:41:08.710
Travel here
is like everything else.

01:41:09.960 --> 01:41:11.620
lt's in your mind.

01:41:13.560 --> 01:41:15.890
You only have to
close your eyes.

01:41:17.300 --> 01:41:19.630
lf you know
where you're going...

01:41:21.300 --> 01:41:23.070
Looks like we did.

01:41:25.610 --> 01:41:27.230
Where you were...

01:41:29.280 --> 01:41:31.710
l tried everything.
Nothing worked.

01:41:33.450 --> 01:41:34.540
Until

01:41:36.180 --> 01:41:38.050
you tried joining me.

01:41:44.060 --> 01:41:46.490
What some folks
call impossible...

01:41:47.160 --> 01:41:49.490
is what
they haven't seen before.

01:42:32.470 --> 01:42:34.460
TRACKER: Excuse me, lady.

01:42:36.510 --> 01:42:38.950
Ready for that surprise
l promised?

01:42:39.780 --> 01:42:40.870
Yeah.

01:42:44.620 --> 01:42:46.590
That's not the surprise!

01:42:47.290 --> 01:42:48.450
Mommy?

01:43:37.840 --> 01:43:40.240
ANNIE: l want us to
grow old together.

01:43:40.310 --> 01:43:42.440
Can we do that here?
Mmm-hmm.

01:43:43.580 --> 01:43:45.070
l want it all.

01:43:46.250 --> 01:43:48.240
As long as it's with you.

01:43:48.680 --> 01:43:50.050
lt will be.

01:43:54.220 --> 01:43:56.250
But what about going back?

01:43:57.490 --> 01:43:58.960
Being reborn?

01:44:00.260 --> 01:44:02.960
That's the one thing
we can't have here.

01:44:03.960 --> 01:44:07.160
Finding each other
all over again.

01:44:08.000 --> 01:44:09.600
Falling in love.

01:44:11.840 --> 01:44:13.740
Make different choices.

01:44:19.010 --> 01:44:20.040
Try again.

01:44:20.180 --> 01:44:21.270
Yeah.

01:44:21.820 --> 01:44:23.580
Avoid sharp objects.

01:44:26.850 --> 01:44:28.190
Don't worry about the kids.

01:44:28.360 --> 01:44:29.950
They'll be here.

01:44:30.020 --> 01:44:31.750
They want us to go.

01:44:33.090 --> 01:44:35.690
A human life
is just a heartbeat here.

01:44:36.430 --> 01:44:37.830
And we'll all be together.

01:44:37.900 --> 01:44:39.130
Forever.

